author: COMSOL
description: A piezoelectric speaker, colloquially known as a piezo buzzer, is a type of piezoelectric transducer that uses a piezoelectric crystal attached to a membrane. The movement of the crystal induces bending of the membrane and thus generates acoustic pressure waves. This model simulates an axisymmetric buzzer intended for ultrasonic applications. This type of transducers is typically driven at the resonance frequency, where the electric power is efficiently converted into radiated sound. A frequency sweep is used to help identify the resonance frequency. The radiation characteristics of the transducer are analyzed in terms of e.g. the beamwidth.
label: piezoacoustic_transducer.mph
